instruction:
An `if` runs code when the condition is true. But what about when it is false?

That is what `else` is for. One or the other will always run — never both, never neither.

```
if age >= 18 {
    fmt.Println("Can borrow adult books")
} else {
    fmt.Println("Children's section only")
}
```

Change `age` to 10 and run it. Then change it to 25 and run it again.

